Here's a Python script for a Discord bot using Discord.js v14 and the slash commands mechanism:

```
import { Client, Intents } from "discord.js"
import { createCommandHandler } from "discord-slash"

const client = new Client({ intents: [Intents.FLAGS.GUILDS] })
const handler = createCommandHandler(client, {
  commandOptions: [
    {
      optionType: "USER",
      description: "The user to ban",
      required: true,
    },
    {
      optionType: "INTEGER",
      description: "The amount of days to ban the user for (in days)",
      required: true,
    },
  ],
})
handler.addCommand(new (client as any).Command("ban", {
  description: "Bans the user provided",
  execute(interaction) {
    const user = interaction.options.getUser("user")! as Discord.GuildMember;
    const days = interaction.options.getInteger("days")! as number;
    client.channels.cache.get("ban").send(`${user} was banned for ${days} days!`);
    user.ban({ days: days }); // Ban the user in the specified amount of days, taking into account the time the command was run. In this case, the ban will be active for 30 days from now, which is also when the bot will send the message to the channel. If it's still active in 30 days, it will be revoked by the server administrator.

